result.formatted_address: 18 Yeung Uk Rd, Tsuen Wan, Hong Kong
result.name: Marcos Oyster Bar and Grill

reviews.text: A decent place for a dine out. Food was OK although I wouldn't call it authentic
Nice oyster and ice lemon tea is great
quite tasty bbq ribs, can serve more sides
A very nice restaurant.

I ordered a medium rib eye steak and I got a medium well instead. But even though it's not how I like my steak, it's still decent. The spaghetti carbonara was mediocre. Not really the taste I remember in Italy. Maybe the chef tries to please the pallet of the majority hk people. The service was OK. I didn't feel like I was being served in a proper ristorante Italiano though. However, we enjoyed the live music performed by the guitarist. He sang songs in English and Spanish. Didn't recognise any Italian songs... which is surprising given the fact that we were in an Italian restaurant... Nonetheless, the mood was quite nice. Yea maybe I'm a little bit to picky but please don't hesitate to try it out yourself. You may actually like it.
